&lt;p>In this activity, citizens locate and tag historical advertisements published in the newspapers in order to reconstruct the commercial landscape of early 20th century Tyrol. Many shops from those times still exist today! This activity makes use of an existing third-party platform, &lt;a href="https://www.historypin.org/en/">Historypin&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>You will need&lt;/strong>:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Basic knowledge of German and Fraktur script&lt;/li>
&lt;li>A free &lt;a href="https://www.historypin.org" target="_blank">Historypin&lt;/a> account&lt;/li>
&lt;li>A desktop computer (activity not designed for mobile devices)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>To add &lt;a href="https://commul.github.io/all4ling/all4ling/projects/zeitshift/historypin/#32-tags">specific tags&lt;/a> and/or location information to the newspaper adverts&lt;/li>
